[Q{HrVXZmGAf~ygtP`hW.text: Why 20.0 instead of 20?Putting in "20" causes only intergers to be chosen. (Because it makes the possible numbers an int, rather than a double.)Putting in "20.0" allows doubles to be chosen. (A double is any real number, so decimals can be chosen randomly.)
